  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 5.5,
      "text": "Now, let's get precise, because prompt is the mold as a nice metaphor, but it's incomplete."
    },
    {
      "start": 7.6,
      "end": 13.58,
      "text": "In PDD, the mold has three components, three types of capital you're accumulating."
    },
    {
      "start": 15.18,
      "end": 18.36,
      "text": "First, tests. Tests are the walls of your mold."
    },
    {
      "start": 19.64,
      "end": 23.46,
      "text": "Each test is a constraint. A boundary the generated code cannot cross."
    },
    {
      "start": 25.14,
      "end": 31.62,
      "text": "When the model generates code, it sees these tests. The code it produces must pass them."
    },
    {
      "start": 32.0,
      "end": 35.08,
      "text": "It literally cannot generate code that violates these walls."
    },
    {
      "start": 36.4,
      "end": 43.1,
      "text": "Now, here's where it gets interesting. When you find a bug, you don't patch the code."
    },
    {
      "start": 43.68,
      "end": 52.26,
      "text": "You add a wall. That wall is permanent. That bug can never occur again, not in this generation."
    },
    {
      "start": 53.22,
      "end": 55.2,
      "text": "Not in any future generation."
    },
    {
      "start": 56.94,
      "end": 62.86,
      "text": "This is the ratchet effect. Tests only accumulate. The mold only gets more precise."
    },
    {
      "start": 63.48,
      "end": 66.34,
      "text": "Each wall you add constrains all future generations."
    },
    {
      "start": 68.1,
      "end": 75.7,
      "text": "In traditional development, a bug fix helps one place. In PDD, a test prevents that bug everywhere,"
    },
    {
      "start": 75.7,
      "end": 80.92,
      "text": "forever. Second, the prompt. Your specification of what you want."
    },
    {
      "start": 81.14,
      "end": 87.38,
      "text": "The prompt doesn't define the walls. Tests do that. The prompt defines what you're asking for and why."
    },
    {
      "start": 89.6,
      "end": 96.4,
      "text": "And here's something subtle. The exact implementation can vary. What's locked is the behavior."
    },
    {
      "start": 97.22,
      "end": 104.0,
      "text": "The code is flexible. The contract is fixed. A good prompt is much smaller than the code it generates."
    },
    {
      "start": 104.0,
      "end": 112.38,
      "text": "You're specifying what and why, not how. Third, grounding. This determines the properties of"
    },
    {
      "start": 112.38,
      "end": 118.74,
      "text": "what fills the mold. Grounding is learned from your past generations. When you successfully"
    },
    {
      "start": 118.74,
      "end": 125.08,
      "text": "generate and fix code, that knowledge feeds back into the system. Your style, your patterns,"
    },
    {
      "start": 125.74,
      "end": 131.52,
      "text": "your team's conventions. Grounding captures all of it and applies it automatically to future"
    },
    {
      "start": 131.52,
      "end": 139.24,
      "text": "generations. Prompt plus tests plus grounding. Intent plus constraints plus style. Together,"
    },
    {
      "start": 139.6,
      "end": 145.74,
      "text": "they form a complete specification. The code is output. The mold is what matters."
    }
  ]
}